Midwest Investment Management - Cleveland, Ohio - Portfolio Management and Investment Advice - Employment Opportunities



























































Employment Opportunities




Currently, there are no open positions at Midwest Investment Management LLC.

General Description of our Firm

Midwest Investment Management LLC is a Cleveland, Ohio, Registered Investment
Advisory (RIA) firm founded in 2000. Our team of investment professionals work
together to provide conservative, independent investment management
services. We have a “client first” culture and team approach with an advisory fee based
revenue model. We build successful long term relationships with high net worth
individuals, small and medium sized private business owners, their company retirement
plans, trusts, and endowments. We have an audited performance track record that
demonstrates a compelling value proposition, confirming our investment management
philosophy and disciplines.


Midwest Investment Management LLC is an Equal Opportunity Employer.


 















Midwest Investment Management - Cleveland, Ohio - Portfolio Management and Investment Advice - Peter A. Vanden Broeck



























































Managing Director



Peter A. Vanden Broeck Managing Director

Peter A. Vanden Broeck joined Midwest Investment Management LLC as Managing Director in May 2013. His career spans more than 30 years and includes investment and portfolio management roles with several major Wall Street investment advisory and brokerage firms.   


He is an experienced portfolio manager, known for his strong commitment to intensive equity research on behalf of his clients. 


“At Midwest Investment Management,” said Mr. Vanden Broeck, “I collaborate with like-minded people who view fundamental security analysis as the foundation for stock selection.   We also share the view that owning stocks represents the partial ownership of a business.”

“In fact,” Mr. Vanden Broeck added, “we pride ourselves on owning the same investments as our clients.  It raises the threshold of examination.”

“We generate new investment ideas by spending countless hours reading periodicals, company filings, and other materials, resulting in detailed analysis and disciplined valuations,” Mr. Vanden Broeck noted.  “We identify facts that we really need to know, and stick to companies whose economics we understand.”

Mr. Vanden Broeck holds a BA in Economics from Macalaster College in St. Paul, Minnesota and has completed additional course work at The University of Paris-Sorbonne.  He is a trustee of the Ratner School in Pepper Pike and past treasurer of the Shaker Lakes Nature Center. He resides with his family in Shaker Heights.


Mr. Vanden Broeck   can be reached at 


Email address protected by JavaScript.
    Please enable JavaScript to contact me.

 or (216) 830-1131.















Midwest Investment Management - Cleveland, Ohio - Portfolio Management and Investment Advice - Introduction



























































Introduction



There are many reasons why people seek and need the services of a professional investment management firm.


Norman F. Klopp
Managing Partner

Whatever your reason, its a decision that requires very serious, thoughtful evaluation and consideration.  Thats why you should get to know our firm.
The Partners are seasoned, experienced investment professionals. Prior to forming the company in January 2000, they worked together as a team for many years.
The firm is 100% owned by its Partners who, collectively, have over 150 years of investment management experience.













