Company Partners



Meg E. Halloran Partner
As Director of Portfolio Management, Meg Halloran has responsibility for the day-to-day management of client accounts at Midwest Investment Management.
Prior to joining Midwest Investment Management, Meg worked at Key Banks headquarters where she administered over $1.6 billion in assets for defined benefit plans, defined contribution plans, and charitable accounts.
Midwest Investment Managements disciplined investment philosophy and its demonstrated commitment to personal service were instrumental in my decision to join the firm, Ms. Halloran noted.  The Partners long-held philosophy of seeking long-term growth, while remaining vigilant to the risk of stock market volatility, is very compatible with my own investment style.
Ms. Halloran received her undergraduate degree in Business Administration from the University of Dayton and her MBA in finance from the Weatherhead School of Management at Case Western Reserve University in Cleveland.
Ms. Halloran is a resident of University Heights where she lives with her husband, Peter, daughter, Katherine, and son, Ryan.  In her free moments she and her husband enjoy snow skiing.
Ms. Halloran can be reached at 
								

